sentence: In 1999 New Zealand general election when Jeanette Fitzsimons contested the (usually New Zealand National Party) seat of Coromandel for the Green Party of Aotearoa New Zealand, it seemed that the Greens ' chances of entering parliament were dependent on Fitzsimons ' performance in Coromandel; in order to receive proportional representation, the party needed to either gain five percent of the national vote or win an electorate seat, and it appeared that the former option was unlikely.
